column1: I'll say. The heat has crept into my bones.
This really melts the stress away.
I miss the place near Leblanc.

I've learned a valuable lesson on this journey:
Sometimes, you simply need to enjoy being
naked.

Yeah, that bath was pretty solid. We should go
again when we're in town.

Anyways, it's nice havin' a bath like this all to
ourselves. Can't get that at home.

What's more, we're in the middle of a long
journey. We must take proper measures to
recover our strength and stamina...

I can hear voices coming from the
girl's side...

What cheat codes did you use to get those?
Dieting lifehacks? You're so skinny, yet—

Could you stop drawing attention to me? 
Go bother Haru instead—hers are no
different.

Haru, not bad! These could knock someone
flat!

Would you please keep it down?
Remember, it's not only us in here.

I refuse to leave right as the true test of
fortitude begins. I shall remain until
I'm ready to faint.

The hell are you talkin' about? If you faint, that's
on you, man.

Uh, y-yeah! They do! A-And for sure that's got
nothin' to do with what we just heard!

Aw, thanks. I've really been workin' these abs...
Wait, what?

Man, this water feels great. Morgana really
shoulda been here.

Sophia might like it as well. Though, being
incorporeal may pose a challenge.

She really is a mystery, ain't she? What're your
thoughts on her?

That much is obvious, but didn't she say
somethin' about wanting to understand
people's hearts?

Ah, the heart of mankind... Try as I may, I have
yet to depict its full essence in my paintings.

It hides both darkness and light, mingling
beauty and atrocity in its depths. Try as you may
to unravel it, its enigma grows deeper still.
Hmmm... Not sure I can comment on that.

But I do know Sophia gets along with all of us.
Gets me thinkin' she might not need to worry
'bout all that heart stuff.
It's to become a good companion.
She does it so she can grow.

Does she not endeavor to become humanity's
companion?

Perhaps she wishes to uncover the workings of
the heart in order to achieve this.

Indeed. Perhaps she wishes to uncover the
workings of the heart in order to achieve her
goal.

That is indeed a logical conclusion, particularly
for a sentient program. Understanding the heart
would certainly prove helpful.

Uhh... Yeah, what you said. She seems pretty
dead-set on it, too.

If that's what Sophia has decided, we should
lend her our full support. She is our precious
ally, after all.

Heh, true enough. She could use all the help she
can get.

Damn... The heat's startin' to get to me. Wanna
ditch the bath and grab some milk coffee?

Whoa, that sounds good too! Now I can't make
up my mind...

I protest. We are in Hokkaido, as you may recall.
It would be a sin to forego its fresh dairy
offerings for some artificial substitute.

To appreciate it properly, we must partake
right as it's squeezed from the udder—the
way farmers have done for millennia!
Uh, yeah... Knock yourself out, man.
